    "description": "Although it is a music game, it does not require complicated controls.<br />\r\nAlthough memorizing the musical score can give you an advantage.<br />\r\nEverything proceeds as you see it.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen two or more circles overlap, the Pressing any key restores the life of the circle.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPressing a key when none of the circles overlap will decrease the life of the circle.<br />\r\nThe same thing happens over time.<br />\r\nThe game is over when the life of one of the circles is exhausted.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEven if the sequence of stationary circles is simple, the speed of the passing circles differs.<br />\r\nIn addition, moving circles overlap each other, creating a complex polyrhythm.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBy the time you reach the final stage, an unprecedented experience awaits you.<br />\r\nRecommended for those who are tired of music games that require only precise movements.<br />\r\nNeither the difficulty nor the ease of existing music games exist here.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt also has the ability to adjust sound delay and other functions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n6 stages<br />\r\n6 original songs<br />\r\nYou may feel that the number of stages is small.<br />\r\nHowever, from around stage 2, it becomes difficult to clear a stage in one go.<br />\r\nAlso, all stages can be selected from the beginning.",
